WEBVTT

00:12.167 --> 00:14.200
PREVIOUSLY
ON "GREY'S ANATOMY..."

00:14.233 --> 00:15.033
DIVORCE PAPERS.

00:15.067 --> 00:16.533
THE BALL'S IN YOUR COURT.
IF YOU SIGN,

00:16.567 --> 00:18.367
I'LL SIGN AND BE ON
THE FIRST PLANE OUT OF HERE.

00:18.400 --> 00:20.300
WOULD YOU LIKE TO GO OUT
WITH ME TONIGHT?

00:20.333 --> 00:21.667
THE HOSPITAL GRANTS YOU

00:21.700 --> 00:23.300
FOUR MONTHS TO RETAKE
THE MEDICAL BOARD EXAM.

00:23.333 --> 00:25.233
WHAT HAPPENS IF I DON'T PASS
THE SECOND TIME?

00:25.267 --> 00:27.167
YOU WILL NO LONGER BE A SURGICAL
RESIDENT AT SEATTLE GRACE.

00:27.200 --> 00:29.100
YOU LOOK GREAT.
THANKS.

00:29.133 --> 00:30.400
ARE YOU OKAY?
YEAH. YOU READY TO GO?

00:30.433 --> 00:33.400
I DIDN'T LIE.
YOU WITHHELD THE TRUTH.
HOW DID I KNOW YOU WERE--

00:33.433 --> 00:35.233
I DISTINCTLY REMEMBER YOU
BREAKING THINGS OFF WITH ME.

00:35.267 --> 00:36.500
(Woman) DR. YANG.
CRISTINA.

00:36.533 --> 00:38.100
(Addison) IT WAS
AN EXTRAUTERINE PREGNANCY.

00:38.133 --> 00:39.367
SHE'S BLEEDING OUT.

00:39.400 --> 00:42.033
I DON'T THINK
I'M SUPPOSED TO BE HERE.
NO. NO, YOU'RE NOT.

00:42.067 --> 00:44.367
(Addison) I DON'T WANT SOMEONE
WHO DOESN'T WANT ME, MEREDITH,

00:44.400 --> 00:46.333
BUT IF THERE'S THE SLIGHTEST
CHANCE THAT HE DOES,

00:46.367 --> 00:48.800
I'M NOT LEAVING SEATTLE.

00:49.833 --> 00:52.433
(thunder rumbles)

00:52.467 --> 00:55.100
(Meredith)
PAIN COMES IN ALL FORMS...

00:55.133 --> 00:57.300
I HAD A GOOD TIME. REALLY.

00:57.333 --> 00:59.300
THANK YOU. IT WAS JUST
THE PERFECT EVENING.

00:59.333 --> 01:01.500
BEST DATE EVER. EVER.
IZZIE.

01:01.533 --> 01:03.433
YOU KNOW, I ESPECIALLY
LIKED THE PART

01:03.467 --> 01:05.733
WHERE YOU TREATED ME
LIKE CRAP THE ENTIRE NIGHT.

01:05.767 --> 01:07.433
THAT WAS FUN.
I HAD A GOOD TIME.

01:07.467 --> 01:09.133
REALLY?

01:09.167 --> 01:10.100
YEAH.

01:10.133 --> 01:11.600
THE SMALL TWINGE,

01:11.633 --> 01:14.167
A BIT OF SORENESS,
THE RANDOM PAIN,

01:14.200 --> 01:16.600
THE NORMAL PAINS WE LIVE WITH
EVERY DAY...

01:16.633 --> 01:18.700
I GOTTA GO.

01:18.733 --> 01:20.333
***

01:20.367 --> 01:23.200
SERIOUSLY?

01:23.233 --> 01:25.133
SERIOUSLY?

01:25.167 --> 01:27.767
THEN THERE'S THE KIND OF PAIN
YOU CAN'T IGNORE.

01:27.800 --> 01:30.133
SERIOUSLY?
A LEVEL OF PAIN SO GREAT

01:30.167 --> 01:32.667
MOVE OVER.
THAT IT BLOCKS OUT
EVERYTHING ELSE...

01:32.700 --> 01:35.133
OH, I WAS SLEEPING.
OH, SHUT UP.

01:35.167 --> 01:36.500
(thunder rumbles)

01:36.533 --> 01:39.567
MAKES THE REST OF THE WORLD
FADE AWAY...

01:39.600 --> 01:41.333
I DON'T WANT TO HAVE
THIS CONVERSATION AGAIN.
MEREDITH.

01:41.367 --> 01:43.267
YOU DIDN'T SIGN
THE DIVORCE PAPERS.

01:43.300 --> 01:45.333
FINE. I GET IT.
END OF DISCUSSION.
MEREDITH.

01:45.367 --> 01:47.133
WHAT?!

01:47.167 --> 01:49.067
UNTIL ALL
WE CAN THINK ABOUT...

01:49.100 --> 01:51.067
OH.
IS HOW MUCH WE HURT...

01:51.067 --> 01:52.800
I USUALLY JUST SAY "MEREDITH,"
AND THEN YOU YELL AT ME.

01:52.833 --> 01:55.067
I HAVEN'T THOUGHT
PAST THAT POINT.

01:55.100 --> 01:57.567
I ACTUALLY DIDN'T
HAVE ANYTHING PLANNED.

01:57.600 --> 01:58.767
HOW WE MANAGE OUR PAIN
IS UP TO US.

01:58.800 --> 02:01.167
WHAT IS THAT?
HEY, STOP IT!

02:01.200 --> 02:03.567
SERIOUSLY?! SERIOUSLY?

02:03.600 --> 02:04.700
SERIOUSLY?

02:04.733 --> 02:08.233
THIS IS A VERY SMALL BED.

02:08.267 --> 02:10.167
HE'S A BRAIN SURGEON.

02:10.200 --> 02:14.067
I LOOK FANTASTIC.
I SHAVED MY LEGS.

02:14.067 --> 02:16.667
HE'S A BRAIN SURGEON.
HOW CAN HE BE SO BRAINLESS?

02:16.700 --> 02:18.600
HELLO? SERIOUSLY.

02:18.633 --> 02:19.800
SERIOUSLY.

02:19.833 --> 02:21.633
SHH.

02:21.667 --> 02:23.600
(thunder rumbles)

02:23.633 --> 02:25.433
PAIN...

02:25.467 --> 02:26.767
WE ANESTHETIZE,

02:26.800 --> 02:30.167
RIDE IT OUT, EMBRACE IT,

02:30.200 --> 02:32.100
IGNORE IT...

02:32.133 --> 02:35.067
***

02:37.300 --> 02:40.167
AND FOR SOME OF US,
THE BEST WAY TO MANAGE PAIN

02:40.200 --> 02:42.533
IS JUST TO PUSH THROUGH IT.

02:42.567 --> 02:45.467
***

02:48.567 --> 02:49.733
YOU'RE DRIPPIN'.
I'M BACK.

02:49.767 --> 02:52.733
I JUST WANNA MAKE THAT CLEAR.
I'M BACK. I'M READY TO WORK.

02:52.767 --> 02:55.300
HAS ANYONE SEEN DR. SHEPHERD
THIS MORNING?

02:55.333 --> 02:57.233
HIS NAME'S ON THE O.R. BOARD.
HE SHOULD BE HERE SOMEWHERE.

02:57.267 --> 02:59.167
I'M GOOD.
I'M READY TO SCRUB IN.

02:59.200 --> 03:00.733
I'M 100% ON TOP OF MY GAME.

03:00.767 --> 03:02.067
YOU JUST GOT DISCHARGED.

03:02.067 --> 03:03.700
PACE YOURSELF.
I'M PACED. I'M PACED.

03:03.733 --> 03:05.767
MM-HMM. ROUNDS, PEOPLE.

03:07.500 --> 03:09.733
WHAT? YOU'RE NOT
TALKIN' TO ME ANYMORE?

03:09.767 --> 03:12.567
OKAY, WHAT HAPPENED LAST NIGHT?
WHAT IS GOING ON WITH YOU?

03:12.600 --> 03:14.233
I'M FINE.

03:14.267 --> 03:16.167
WHAT'S YOUR PROBLEM?

03:16.200 --> 03:18.700
FINE.
YOU KNOW WHAT, ALEX?

03:18.733 --> 03:20.667
NO, I'M NOT
TALKING TO YOU ANYMORE.

03:23.233 --> 03:25.167
AHEM. DR. BAILEY?

03:25.200 --> 03:28.700
HENRY LAMOTT, AGE 42,
IS SCHEDULED WITH DR. SHEPHERD

03:28.733 --> 03:31.833
FOR A SPINAL IMPLANT TO CONTROL
THE PAIN OF HIS HERNIATED DISC,

03:31.867 --> 03:33.767
IS ALLERGIC TO
ALL PAIN MEDICATION.

03:33.800 --> 03:35.433
(sexy music playing)
IS THAT...

03:35.467 --> 03:38.200
PORN.
PORN?

03:38.233 --> 03:39.733
AS IN "PORN"?
ALL RIGHT.

03:39.767 --> 03:41.600
WHAT ARE WE WATCHING?

03:41.633 --> 03:42.833
KAREV, GO STAND
IN THE HALL.

03:42.867 --> 03:45.067
UH, MR. AND MRS. LAMOTT,

03:45.067 --> 03:46.800
I'M SURE YOU ARE
REALLY NICE PEOPLE,

03:46.833 --> 03:49.400
AND WHAT YOU DO
IN THE PRIVACY OF YOUR OWN--

03:49.433 --> 03:50.767
(Woman laughs)

03:50.800 --> 03:52.767
LOOK, WE CAN'T HAVE PORN
IN HERE. THIS IS A HOSPITAL.

03:52.800 --> 03:54.700
IT'S FOR MY PAIN.

03:54.733 --> 03:56.633
MY DOC SAYS IT RELEASES
ENDORPHINS IN THE BRAIN,

03:56.667 --> 03:59.300
AND IT HELPS KEEP MY PAIN
AT A MANAGEABLE LEVEL.

03:59.333 --> 04:00.400
REALLY?
(Woman laughing)

04:00.433 --> 04:01.600
GEORGE--HALL.
YEAH.

04:01.633 --> 04:03.633
(Woman moaning)

04:05.500 --> 04:08.267
WHAT IS THIS?

04:08.300 --> 04:11.167
"NASTY, NAUGHTY NURSES..."
UM, "4."

04:11.200 --> 04:14.167
(Women laughing)

04:15.167 --> 04:17.067
THAT DOES NOT
LOOK COMFORTABLE.

04:17.067 --> 04:19.367
TRUST ME, IT'S NOT.

04:19.400 --> 04:21.433
GET IN THE HALL.

04:23.600 --> 04:26.467
***

04:26.500 --> 04:31.067
(Woman) * NOBODY KNOWS
WHERE THEY MIGHT END UP *

04:31.100 --> 04:34.333
* NOBODY KNOWS

04:34.367 --> 04:37.233
Captioning provided by
Touchstone Television
and ABC, Inc.

04:37.267 --> 04:40.167
Captioned by
Closed Captioning Services, Inc.

04:41.867 --> 04:43.633
* OH, OH

04:43.667 --> 04:47.500
* SUPPOSE YOU'LL NEVER KNOW

04:48.800 --> 04:51.200
(thunder rumbles)

04:51.233 --> 04:53.133
O'MALLEY, KAREV,
YOU'RE IN THE PIT TODAY.

04:53.167 --> 04:55.067
STEVENS,
THERE'S A CARDIAC PATIENT

04:55.100 --> 04:56.433
WAITING FOR YOU UP ON TWO.

04:56.467 --> 04:57.800
YANG, KEEP AN EYE
ON THE LAMOTTS.

04:57.833 --> 04:59.533
I DON'T WANT
ANY PROBLEMS. GO.

04:59.567 --> 05:02.500
GREY, YOUR MOTHER'S BEING
DISCHARGED THIS EVENING.

05:02.533 --> 05:04.567
YOU'VE MADE ARRANGEMENTS,
OR DO YOU NEED MORE TIME?

05:04.600 --> 05:06.500
THE NURSING HOME
IS COMING AT 8.

05:06.533 --> 05:09.400
ALL RIGHT. THEN YOU'RE WITH
SHEPHERD--DEREK SHEPHERD TODAY.

05:09.433 --> 05:11.333
HEY, LIFE IS SHORT.
TIMES ARE HARD.

05:11.367 --> 05:13.200
THE ROAD IS LONG
WITH MANY A WINDING TURN.

05:13.233 --> 05:16.067
HE ASKED FOR YOU.
TAKE IT UP WITH HIM.

05:18.567 --> 05:19.600
OKAY.

05:19.633 --> 05:21.400
PETE WILLOUGHBY,

05:21.433 --> 05:24.667
25-YEAR-OLD G.S.W.
TO THE CHEST.

05:24.700 --> 05:27.300
IMMEDIATE RETURN
OF 860 c.c.s OF BLOOD...

05:27.333 --> 05:30.300
OH, MAN, THIS HURTS.
HE'S PUT OUT MORE THAN 200 c.c.s
OVER THE PAST HOUR.

05:30.333 --> 05:32.500
THEY NEVER TELL YOU IN MOVIES
HOW MUCH IT HURTS TO GET SHOT.

05:32.533 --> 05:34.433
PUSH MORPHINE, 2 MILLIGRAMS.
ALEX, THIS IS MY CASE.

05:34.467 --> 05:36.767
MORPHINE, 5 MILLIGRAMS.
YOU DIDN'T EVEN CALL HIM.

05:36.800 --> 05:39.567
I DON'T HAVE TO CALL HIM.
I WAS HERE FIRST.

05:39.600 --> 05:40.633
YOU GOT HERE FIRST BECAUSE
I LET YOU.

05:40.667 --> 05:42.733
WHERE'S THE CHEST FILMS?
UNH.

05:42.767 --> 05:44.667
I GOT 'EM.
YOU ALWAYS GET THE SURGERY.

05:44.700 --> 05:47.200
TODAY,
I'M GETTING A SURGERY.
GUYS, KNOCK IT OFF.

05:47.233 --> 05:48.667
HE'S ONE OF SEATTLE'S FINEST.

05:48.700 --> 05:51.500
YOU'VE GOT AN ENTIRE
POLICE FORCE WATCHING YOU.

05:53.800 --> 05:56.067
(George) PAGE DR. BURKE.

05:56.067 --> 05:58.133
LET HIM KNOW I'M BRINGIN' UP
A G.S.W.

05:58.167 --> 06:00.667
THAT WE ARE BRINGING UP
A G.S.W.

06:02.467 --> 06:05.367
LOOKS LIKE YOU'LL BE ABLE
TO GO HOME TODAY, ELLIS.

06:05.400 --> 06:07.433
BUT I STILL
HAVE PATIENTS TO SEE.

06:07.467 --> 06:09.333
NO. NO MORE PATIENTS.

06:09.367 --> 06:12.200
I'LL BE BACK
TO CHECK ON YOU LATER, OKAY?

06:12.233 --> 06:14.067
YOU SHOULD KNOW I'M THINKING
OF LEAVING THATCHER.

06:14.100 --> 06:17.100
I SHOULD NEVER
HAVE MARRIED HIM.

06:17.133 --> 06:20.633
I'LL LEAVE HIM, YOU LEAVE ADELE.
THEN WHEN OUR RESIDENCY'S OVER,

06:20.667 --> 06:23.067
WE CAN BOTH GET JOBS
AT THE SAME HOSPITAL.

06:23.100 --> 06:25.133
WHY DON'T YOU GET HER MEDS
READY FOR DISCHARGE, NURSE?

06:25.167 --> 06:26.400
THANK YOU.

06:26.433 --> 06:30.333
(Woman) DR. CHIN, TWO WEST.
DR. CHIN, TWO WEST.

06:31.667 --> 06:35.533
ELLIS... THAT WAS
A LONG TIME AGO, REMEMBER?

06:35.567 --> 06:38.167
WE HAD THIS DISCUSSION
21 YEARS AGO.

06:38.200 --> 06:40.733
THINK ABOUT IT, RICHARD.
WE SHOULD MAKE THE BREAK NOW.

06:40.767 --> 06:42.667
IF WE WAIT
UNTIL RESIDENCY'S OVER,

06:42.700 --> 06:44.600
YOU'LL BE AT ONE HOSPITAL,
AND I'LL BE AT ANOTHER.

06:44.633 --> 06:45.667
WE COULD END UP

06:45.700 --> 06:49.133
AT OPPOSITE ENDS OF THE COUNTRY.
IT'LL BE TOO LATE.

06:52.433 --> 06:55.267
(elevator bell dings)
MEREDITH.

06:55.300 --> 06:57.200
YOUR WIFE
IS LOOKING FOR YOU.
OH, MY GOD.

06:57.233 --> 06:59.533
THIS IS HARD
FOR ME, MEREDITH.
WELL, LET ME
MAKE IT EASY, THEN.

06:59.567 --> 07:01.467
I'M NOT GONNA BE
THAT WOMAN--

07:01.500 --> 07:03.433
THE ONE WHO BREAKS UP A MARRIAGE
OR BEGS YOU TO WANT ME.

07:03.467 --> 07:06.700
YOU CAN SIGN THE PAPERS OR
YOU CANNOT. THE CHOICE IS YOURS.

07:06.733 --> 07:09.333
EITHER WAY, WHEN IT COMES
TO THIS RELATIONSHIP, I'M OUT.

07:09.367 --> 07:10.767
NOW WHERE'S THIS PATIENT

07:10.800 --> 07:12.700
I'M SUPPOSED
TO BE HELPING YOU WITH?

07:12.733 --> 07:14.500
DOWN THERE.

07:15.567 --> 07:18.200
YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE TRIED
TO WALK THE DOG IN THE RAIN.

07:18.233 --> 07:21.100
OH, LOU, IT WASN'T THE RAIN.
I JUST PASSED OUT.

07:21.133 --> 07:22.833
ACTUALLY, MRS. BRADLEY--
VERNA.

07:22.867 --> 07:25.800
VERNA, YOU PRESENTED
WITH LATERAL S.T. ELEVATIONS

07:25.833 --> 07:28.433
AND RECIPROCAL INFERIOR CHANGES
CONSISTENT WITH AN M.I.--

07:28.467 --> 07:30.367
A HEART ATTACK.
(Lou) OH, MY GOD.

07:30.400 --> 07:32.167
LOU, DON'T WORRY. COME ON.

07:32.200 --> 07:34.100
I'VE HAD THESE LITTLE
CHEST PAINS BEFORE,

07:34.133 --> 07:36.600
AND IT TURNED OUT TO BE NOTHING.
THIS IS NOTHING.

07:38.667 --> 07:41.267
LOU, NOT IN FRONT
OF THE DOCTOR.

07:41.300 --> 07:43.733
I'VE HAD A TWINGE
IN MY BACK FOR AWHILE.

07:43.767 --> 07:45.667
I THOUGHT IT WOULD GO AWAY,

07:45.700 --> 07:47.600
BUT THEN LAST NIGHT,
MY LEGS WENT NUMB,

07:47.633 --> 07:51.300
AND THIS MORNING, MY BACK--
THE PAIN IS JUST TOO MUCH.

07:51.333 --> 07:53.233
MS. CHUE, LET ME PUT YOU
ON A P.C.A. PUMP,

07:53.267 --> 07:55.533
GIVE YOU SOME MORPHINE, WHICH
SHOULD HELP CONTROL THE PAIN.

07:55.567 --> 07:57.167
THANK YOU.

07:57.200 --> 07:59.633
BUT THERE'S A GREATER
PROBLEM HERE.

07:59.667 --> 08:02.300
I'VE JUST TAKEN A LOOK
AT YOUR M.R.I.--
ANNA...

08:02.333 --> 08:04.300
WHY DIDN'T YOU CALL US
BEFORE COMING DOWN HERE?

08:04.333 --> 08:05.600
I'M SORRY.

08:05.633 --> 08:08.133
THESE ARE MY PARENTS.
HI.

08:08.167 --> 08:11.067
WHAT'S GOING ON?
I WAS JUST ABOUT TO EXPLAIN
THAT ANNA'S M.R.I.

08:11.067 --> 08:13.833
HAS SHOWN THAT SHE HAS
A MYXOPAPILLARY EPENDYMOMA--

08:13.867 --> 08:15.767
IT'S A TUMOR
IN HER SPINAL CANAL,

08:15.800 --> 08:17.533
BUT THE GOOD NEWS
IS THAT WE CAN OPERATE.

08:17.567 --> 08:19.733
YOU HAVE A 95% CHANCE
OF FULLY RECOVERING

08:19.767 --> 08:22.533
IF WE GET YOU INTO SURGERY
AS SOON AS POSSIBLE.

08:22.567 --> 08:24.400
WE CAN'T WAIT ANOTHER MOMENT.
WITH A TUMOR THIS AGGRESSIVE,

08:24.433 --> 08:26.333
EVEN WAITING ANOTHER DAY
PUTS YOU AT RISK

08:26.367 --> 08:28.467
FOR PERMANENT PARALYSIS.

08:28.500 --> 08:30.233
FATHER?

08:30.267 --> 08:32.400
NO.

08:32.433 --> 08:34.067
NO SURGERY.

08:34.067 --> 08:36.800
MR. CHUE, WITHOUT SURGERY,
ANNA WILL BE PARALYZED

08:36.833 --> 08:39.133
PROBABLY WITHIN
THE NEXT 24 HOURS.

08:39.167 --> 08:41.500
THERE'LL BE NO SURGERY TODAY.
WE'RE TAKING HER HOME.

08:41.533 --> 08:44.133
ANNA NEEDS THE SURGERY.
THEN SHE CAN HAVE IT
AT ANOTHER TIME.

08:44.167 --> 08:47.667
LOOK, MR. CHUE--
WE ARE TAKING
OUR DAUGHTER HOME.

08:50.267 --> 08:52.100
ANNA, YOU'VE OVER 18.

08:52.133 --> 08:54.067
YOU DON'T NEED
YOUR FATHER'S CONSENT.

08:57.133 --> 08:59.700
I'M HMONG, AND MY FATHER
IS THE ELDER.

08:59.733 --> 09:01.633
IF HE SAYS I GO HOME,

09:01.667 --> 09:03.200
I GO HOME.

09:07.200 --> 09:09.100
HMONG? LET'S FIND OUT
WHAT THAT MEANS.
OKAY.

09:09.133 --> 09:11.067
CONTACT SOCIAL SERVICES.
SEE IF WE CAN GET

09:11.067 --> 09:12.767
SOMEBODY DOWN HERE
TO TALK TO HIM.

09:12.800 --> 09:14.700
DO I CONTINUE TO PROCESS
HER DISCHARGE?
YEAH, WE HAVE TO.

09:14.733 --> 09:16.633
IT'S INSANE, BUT WE HAVE TO.
IT REMINDS ME OF THIS CASE

09:16.667 --> 09:18.567
I HAD IN NEW YORK ONE TIME WHERE
THIS WOMAN CAME TO THE OFFICE--

09:18.600 --> 09:21.333
LOOK, DO YOU NEED ME FOR
ANYTHING ELSE WORK RELATED?

09:24.267 --> 09:26.600
LOOK, I WAS MARRIED
FOR 11 YEARS.

09:26.633 --> 09:27.800
ADDISON IS MY FAMILY.

09:27.833 --> 09:30.700
THAT IS 11 THANKSGIVINGS,
11 BIRTHDAYS AND 11 CHRISTMASES,

09:30.733 --> 09:32.767
AND IN ONE DAY, I'M SUPPOSED
TO SIGN A PIECE OF PAPER

09:32.800 --> 09:34.300
AND END MY FAMILY?

09:34.333 --> 09:35.633
A PERSON DOESN'T DO THAT--

09:35.667 --> 09:37.567
NOT WITHOUT
A LITTLE HESITATION.

09:37.600 --> 09:39.500
I'M ENTITLED TO A LITTLE
UNCERTAINTY HERE.

09:39.533 --> 09:41.433
JUST A MOMENT TO UNDERSTAND
THE MAGNITUDE OF WHAT IT MEANS

09:41.467 --> 09:43.367
TO CUT SOMEBODY OUT
OF MY LIFE.

09:43.400 --> 09:45.800
I'M ENTITLED
TO AT LEAST ONE MOMENT...
(door closes)

09:45.833 --> 09:47.733
OF PAINFUL DOUBT.

09:47.767 --> 09:51.133
AND A LITTLE UNDERSTANDING
FROM YOU WOULD BE NICE.

09:53.067 --> 09:55.333
DR. SHEPHERD,
STILL HERE, I SEE.

09:55.367 --> 09:56.700
I COULDN'T LEAVE YOU.

09:56.733 --> 09:58.633
HAVE YOU SEEN
THE OTHER DR. SHEPHERD?

09:58.667 --> 10:00.567
I'LL TELL HIM
YOU'RE LOOKIN' FOR HIM.

10:00.600 --> 10:05.133
SO THANKS FOR, YOU KNOW,
BEING THERE.

10:05.167 --> 10:07.067
NO THANKS NEEDED.

10:07.100 --> 10:08.833
OKAY.
SO WHERE ARE WE?

10:08.867 --> 10:10.767
UH, THE NORTHEAST CORNER
OF THE HOSPITAL.

10:10.800 --> 10:12.667
OH, I-I'M GETTING BACK
ON MY FEET.

10:12.700 --> 10:15.167
FINE.
BUT THAT DOESN'T MEAN THAT--

10:15.200 --> 10:17.367
CRISTINA.
IT'S MY FIRST DAY BACK.

10:17.400 --> 10:19.267
I'M NOT WAITING FOREVER.

10:19.300 --> 10:21.233
***

10:21.267 --> 10:22.600
HEY, KAREV AND O'MALLEY

10:22.633 --> 10:24.533
ARE BRINGING UP A G.S.W.
YOU WANT TO SCRUB IN?

10:24.567 --> 10:25.733
NO CAN DO.
NO EXTRA WORK.

10:25.767 --> 10:28.800
I'M TRYING TO GET OUT OF HERE
AT A DECENT HOUR TONIGHT.

10:28.833 --> 10:30.733
WHAT, YOU GOT A DATE?
YES. YES, I DO.

10:30.767 --> 10:32.267
A HANDSOME MAN
IS WHISKING ME AWAY

10:32.300 --> 10:35.567
TO A LOVE NEST
FOR THE WEEKEND.

10:35.600 --> 10:38.833
YOU GOT SHOT
IN THE LINE OF DUTY?

10:38.867 --> 10:42.633
FIRST MONTH ON THE JOB.
CAN YOU BELIEVE MY LUCK?

10:42.667 --> 10:44.567
GUY PULLS A GUN,
AND I FREEZE UP

10:44.600 --> 10:46.500
THE ROOKIE LET HIMSELF
GET SHOT.

10:46.533 --> 10:48.400
I'M NEVER GONNA
LIVE THIS DOWN.

10:48.433 --> 10:50.333
SURE, YOU WILL.
YOU THINK?

10:50.367 --> 10:53.100
ABSOLUTELY.

10:53.133 --> 10:54.833
***

10:54.867 --> 10:57.100
HEY, I GOT VERNA BRADLEY'S
TESTS BACK.

10:57.133 --> 10:59.100
I DON'T THINK
SHE HAD A HEART ATTACK.

